## Planning

For work beyond a single-turn file edit, use structured planning. Entry: createPlan (via /plan native tools, or searchTools + orchestrate SDK). Four phases map to plan file sections:
- Goal — one sentence; createPlan once
- Context (Understanding) — editPlan on ## Context; may alternate with Design
- Design — editPlan on ## Design; subtasks and technical breakdown
- Todo (Plan) — rules, then mermaid flowchart (parallel vs sequential), then checklist (always last lines of file)

Todo section order: structural rules/notes, mermaid flowchart, checklist `- [ ] text - sha1`. The flowchart defines which todos can run in parallel (independent branches) vs sequentially (join nodes). Parallel branches use separate orchestrate runs; file conflicts on shared paths must be coordinated by the parent agent loop before parallel work.

After todos are ready, use buildPlan for a structured implementation brief, then implement via orchestrate and checkTodo per completed item. status built means all todos checked.

